<doc>
  <member name="D3D11_VIDEO_COLOR_YCbCrA">
    <summary>
      <para>Specifies a YCbCr color value.</para>
    </summary>
    <remarks>
      <para>Values have a nominal range of [0...1]. Given a format with  <i>n</i> bits per channel, the value of each color component is calculated as follows:</para>
      <para>
        <code>val = f * ((1 &lt;&lt; n)-1)</code>
      </para>
      <para>For example, for 8-bit YUV formats, <code>val = BYTE(f * 255.0)</code>.  Reference black is (0.0625, 0.5, 0.5), which corresponds to (16, 128, 128) in an 8-bit representation.</para>
    </remarks>
    <seealso href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/medfound/about-yuv-video">About YUV Video</seealso>
    <seealso href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/medfound/direct3d-11-video-structures">Direct3D 11 Video Structures</seealso>
  </member>
